---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

const breadcrumbs = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "BreadcrumbList",
  "itemListElement": [
    { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 1, "name": "Home", "item": "https://youtubeplaylistfinder.com/" },
    { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 2, "name": "Privacy Policy", "item": "https://youtubeplaylistfinder.com/privacy-policy" }
  ]
};
---

<Layout 
  title="Privacy Policy | youtubeplaylistfinder"
  description="Read the youtubeplaylistfinder.com privacy policy. Understand browser storage, YouTube API usage, and user rights."
  canonical="https://youtubeplaylistfinder.com/privacy-policy"
  schema={breadcrumbs}
>
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto space-y-8 text-left leading-relaxed">
    <section class="border-b border-white/5 pb-6">
      <span class="text-[10px] font-mono uppercase tracking-wider text-text-muted">Legal Information</span>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight text-white mt-1">Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="text-xs text-text-secondary mt-1">Last updated: June 30, 2026</p>
    </section>

    <div class="space-y-6 text-xs text-text-secondary">
      <p>
        At youtubeplaylistfinder.com, we prioritize the privacy and security of our visitors. This statement details the categories of metrics logged, collected, or stored by our services and how we handle third-party integrations.
      </p>

      <div class="space-y-2">
        <h2 class="text-sm font-bold text-white uppercase tracking-wider font-mono">1. LocalStorage & Client Data</h2>
        <p>
          We operate as a client-first application wherever possible to minimize user data storage on central servers. The following metrics are compiled and stored exclusively inside your browser's local cache database (`localStorage`):
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-1">
          <li><strong>Completed Videos</strong>: Progress checkmark arrays mapping YouTube video IDs to save study percentages.</li>
          <li><strong>Saved Playlists</strong>: Slugs representing custom bookmarks added to your learning tracks library.</li>
          <li><strong>Streak Parameters</strong>: Log dates of active study sessions to count consecutive days active.</li>
          <li><strong>Visited History</strong>: Cache history of viewed playlists used to populate dynamic compare selectors.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          This data remains under your absolute control and never gets uploaded to our servers. You can clear this data at any time by clearing your browser site cache.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="space-y-2">
        <h2 class="text-sm font-bold text-white uppercase tracking-wider font-mono">2. Third-Party APIs (YouTube Data API)</h2>
        <p>
          Our platform integrates with YouTube services. By using our website, you agree to be bound by the YouTube Terms of Service and Google Privacy Policy.
        </p>
        <p>
          We do not collect or store personal parameters (such as names or Google accounts) from the YouTube API. We only request public catalog parameters (playlist titles, channel names, video outlines, and thumbnail URLs) to render educational checklists.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="space-y-2">
        <h2 class="text-sm font-bold text-white uppercase tracking-wider font-mono">3. Analytics & Cookie Tracking</h2>
        <p>
          We compile anonymized visitor logs (IP addresses, browser agents, page views, and landing duration) to monitor server load and optimize Core Web Vitals. These metrics do not hold personal identification markers.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="space-y-2">
        <h2 class="text-sm font-bold text-white uppercase tracking-wider font-mono">4. User Rights & Data Deletion</h2>
        <p>
          As we do not hold database profiles for basic users, data rights (GDPR/CCPA access, modification, or erasure) can be exercised directly by clearing your browser's localStorage configurations. For questions, contact us at `support@youtubeplaylistfinder.com`.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
